glosses: to shove, thrust, prod, poke, nudge
to incite, provoke, urge on, stir up, instigate

etymology: From Ottoman Turkish دورتمك (dürtmek, “to push; shove; thrust; poke”), from Proto-Turkic *türt-. Relation in "to push; shove" < "to rub; butter" is unclear. Cognate with Kyrgyz түртүү (türtüü, “to push, poke”), Uzbek turtmoq (“to push, poke”).
